stm32f0-baremetal

The main goal of this source code is to show what's the minimal set of
instructions needed to boot a board based on a ARM MCU.

The target board is STM32F0-Discovery board, and the code shows the following
features:
- project with simple Makefile and linker script;
- boot;
- clock setting;
- uart setup.

The source code makes no usage of any external library and it is suitable for
other ARM boards, with proper modifications.
